ted emission with more than ten-fold accelerated\nradiative decay, extension of the first-order coherence time by more than a\nfactor of four, photon bunching, and delayed emission pulses with Burnham-Chiao\nringing behaviour at high excitation density. These mesoscopically extended\ncoherent states can be employed to boost opto-electronic device performances\nand enable entangled multi-photon quantum light sources.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 5 Apr 2018 14:24:05 GMT"}],"update_date":"2018-11-09"}
