nts is\nfound, from South (NGC 6231) to North (G345.45+1.50). We suggest that the\ndiluted appearance of Trumpler 24 indicates that the cluster is now dissolving\ninto the field, and that tidal stripping by NGC 6231 nearby contributes to the\nprocess.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 5 Apr 2018 15:15:33 GMT"}],"update_date":"2018-08-01"}
